# Hello Puppeteer ğŸ‘‹

```javascript
const puppeteer = require('puppeteer');

(async () => {
  const browser = await puppeteer.launch();
  const page = await browser.newPage();
  await page.goto('https://example.com');
  await page.screenshot({ path: 'example.png' });
  await browser.close();
})();
```

# Actions ğŸ–±ï¸

```javascript
await page.type('#email', 'user@example.com');
await page.click('#submit-btn');
await page.waitForSelector('.success-msg');
```

# Running JS in Browser ğŸ§ 

`page.evaluate()` runs code in the context of the page, giving you access to `window`, `document`, and library objects (like `jQuery`).

```javascript
const dimensions = await page.evaluate(() => {
  return { width: document.body.clientWidth };
});
```

# Mobile View ğŸ“±

```javascript
const iPhone = puppeteer.KnownDevices['iPhone 11'];
await page.emulate(iPhone);
```

Instantly switch to mobile viewports, touch support, and user-agent strings.

# Traffic Control ğŸ“¡

Block images or CSS to speed up scraping, or mock API responses.

```javascript
await page.setRequestInterception(true);
page.on('request', req => {
  if (req.resourceType() === 'image') req.abort();
  else req.continue();
});
```

# Print to File ğŸ“„

```javascript
await page.pdf({
  path: 'report.pdf',
  format: 'A4',
  printBackground: true
});
```

# Dialogs ğŸ“¢

```javascript
page.on('dialog', async dialog => {
  console.log(dialog.message());
  await dialog.dismiss();
});
```

# Auth ğŸ”

```javascript
await page.setCookie({ name: 'token', value: 'secret' });
const cookies = await page.cookies();
```
